  "prompt": "I have a crush on a girl and do not have courage to propose to her. What should I do to tell her that I like her?",
  "response": "Expressing your feelings to someone you have a crush on can be nerve-wracking, but it\u2019s also an important step if you want to build a meaningful relationship. Here are some steps to help you gather the courage and express your feelings in a sincere and respectful way:\n\n### 1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**\n   - Make sure you\u2019re clear about what you want to express. Ask yourself why you like her and what you hope to achieve by telling her.\n\n### 2. **Build Your Confidence**\n   - Remind yourself that it\u2019s okay to feel nervous. Confidence comes from being genuine and true to yourself.\n   - Practice what you want to say, either by writing it down or rehearsing in front of a mirror.\n\n### 3. **Choose the Right Time and Place**\n   - Pick a setting where you both feel comfortable and there\u2019s enough privacy for an honest conversation.\n   - Avoid high-pressure situations or times when she might be distracted.\n\n### 4. **Be Genuine and Honest**\n   - Start with a simple, heartfelt statement like, *\u201cI\u2019ve really enjoyed getting to know you, and I\u2019ve realized that I have feelings for you.\u201d*\n   - Avoid overloading her with too much information or dramatic declarations.\n\n### 5. **Respect Her Response**\n   - Be prepared for any reaction, whether it\u2019s positive, neutral, or even rejection. Respect her feelings and give her space to respond.\n   - If she\u2019s not interested, don\u2019t take it personally. It takes courage to express your feelings, and you should be proud of yourself for trying.\n\n### 6. **Take It Slow**\n   - If she responds positively, take things one step at a time. You don\u2019t need to rush into anything.\n   - If she needs time to process, give her that space without pressuring her.\n\n### 7. **Focus on Building Connection**\n   - If you\u2019re not ready to outright confess your feelings, focus on spending more time with her, getting to know her better, and strengthening your friendship. This can help build trust and comfort between you.\n\n### Example of What to Say:\n*\u201cHey [Her Name], I\u2019ve really enjoyed the time we\u2019ve spent together, and I\u2019ve realized that I like you more than just as a friend. I wanted to be honest with you about how I feel. No pressure at all\u2014I just wanted to share my feelings.\u201d*\n\nRemember, rejection is a possibility, but it\u2019s better to take the chance than to wonder \u201cwhat if?\u201d You\u2019ll grow from the experience, no matter the outcome. Good luck! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
